state_summary: The venture capital market is expected to undergo significant changes in 2026, driven by advancements in AI and global shifts in technology adoption.
evidence: Raising in 2025 requires a shift from “visionary” to “battle-tested.”
Founders must prove to VCs they have more than just traction; they need a distribution advantage.
We expect investor and startup interest to continue at all-time highs.
I do think we will start to see tuck-in acquisitions, acquihires, and wind-downs in highly concentrated sectors such as coding automation, sales automation, marketing, and advertising.
AI will remain a hot topic, barring negative hard catalysts that dramatically change conditions, like an energy crisis or a rise in default rates.
